# Terraform EC2 Instance

This Terraform configuration sets up an EC2 instance in an AWS environment. Follow the instructions below to customize the instance settings and launch it.

## Prerequisites

1. **Install Terraform:** Follow the official [Terraform installation guide](https://learn.hashicorp.com/tutorials/terraform/install-cli) to install Terraform on your system.

2. **AWS Credentials:** Make sure you have your AWS credentials configured. You can set them up using the [AWS CLI](https://docs.aws.amazon.com/cli/latest/userguide/cli-configure-quickstart.html) or environment variables.

## Configuration

1. **Clone this repository:**

2. **Replace variables file with your respective values**

3. **Initialize your backend using terraform init**

4. **Use terraform plan to verify your resources later do terraform apply**
